  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The work entitled \"Imaging the voltage of neurons distributed across entire brains of larval zebrafish\" has garnered a notable academic footprint since its dissemination on bioRxiv. With citations from prestigious venues like Nature Methods and others, it is clear that the research is making significant contributions to the field of neuroscience.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">This study presents groundbreaking techniques for imaging neuronal voltage across the entire brain of larval zebrafish, showcasing an innovative approach that has potential applications in understanding neural circuitry. The research is anchored by esteemed institutions such as the Howard Hughes Medical Institute and the McGovern Institute for Brain Research, highlighting its robust institutional backing.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The impact of this work is reflected in its citations, with a total of 10 according to OpenAlex, indicating that it is being referenced across a variety of influential academic settings, particularly in journals such as Nature Methods and Nature Communications. This suggests a positive reception and a significant role in driving further research in the field of neuroscience.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, the absence of any risk and credibility alerts supports the study\u2019s credibility, suggesting strong methodological foundations. The lack of online mentions and community discourse in platforms such as Reddit and Wikipedia indicates that while the research has not yet reached a broader public audience, its academic significance is recognized within specialized circles.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of data repositories and user-generated discourse, the work\u2019s trajectory in terms of citations and institutional affiliations reflects a favorable trend in its acceptance and usefulness. As the field continues to explore innovative imaging techniques, this research may serve as a foundational output for subsequent studies, contributing to the evolving understanding of neural mechanisms within complex biological systems.</p>",
